Smile when you're sad. Laugh when you want to break down and cry. Dance when you don't want to move. Hug someone you're not close to. Sing in the shower. Run through the sprinklers. Play in the rain. Spin around in circles and fall because you're so dizzy. Give to the needy. Eat junk food. Have sleep overs with friends even when you're older and stay up all night talking about the good times. Love the ones who hurt you. Tell someone off. Take chances. Live life.

I don't know exactly where I stand with you, I don't know what I mean to you, or what I see in you, but I do know that all I think about is you

beginnings are scary, endings are usually sad, but it's the middle that counts

No matter what you do, you will get criticized. So do exactly what you want
to do

After a while you learn that what you really are is all the experiences and all the thoughts you've ever had and all the people who have touched your life no matter how briefly.

Sometimes you just feel everything and nothing all at once. Sometimes you'll find yourself smiling while missing something at the same time. At times you can absolutely love a person, all the while wanting to hate them. Life comes without guarantees, except that smiling with brighten your face, laughing will enhance your eyes, and falling in love will change your life.

Just because something ends doesn't mean it never should have been

Sometimes I wonder why words can mean nothing, and silence can mean everything  

its hard to wait around
for something that you
know won't ever happen
but its harder when you know its
all you want
